cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper investigates the effectiveness of social rating systems, which are commonly used in social media platforms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it uses an internet game to collect data. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper discusses the informativeness of popularity systems. Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software development (cs.SD) are less likely but still possible sub-categories as the paper discusses the limitations and potential biases of social rating systems.
